OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,FJohn Healey has resigned as defence
OL,7,Fsecretary after a row with the prime
OL,8,Fminister over military spending,
OL,9,Faccusing the prime minister of making
OL,10,Fthe county "less safe".
OL,12,FHe wrote to Sir Keir Starmer to resign
OL,13,Ffrom the position with "great regret
OL,14,Fand reluctance", citing disagreements
OL,15,Fabout defence spending ahead of the
OL,16,Frelease of the delayed Defence
OL,17,FInvestment Plan (DIP).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,FHealey said the prime minister has
OL,7,F"been unable... to commit the
OL,8,Fresources that the nation needs to
OL,9,Fdefend the country" and that he has
OL,10,F"no other option" but to resign.
OL,12,FHe added: "I am being forced to make
OL,13,Fdecision that would reduce the
OL,14,Freadiness of our Forces and increase
OL,15,Fthe risk to personnel on operations,
OL,16,Fand could make the country less safe."
OL,18,FA former government minister close to
OL,19,FHealey has said: "John is one of the
OL,20,Fmost principled MPs I know - this is a
OL,21,Fmatter of principle for him.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,F"Country before party. He has
OL,7,Fdemonstrated that again today".
OL,9,FHealey posted his letter to the prime
OL,10,Fminister on social media, which read:
OL,11,F"This new era for defence required
OL,12,Ffurther investment through the Defence
OL,13,FInvestment Plan.
OL,15,F"The excellent and extensive cross-
OL,16,Fgovernment work that completed in
OL,17,FJanuary ` overseen by you, me and the
OL,18,FChancellor ` confirmed the scale of
OL,19,Fthe challenge and the rising demands
OL,20,Fon defence".
OL,26,@sD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,FHe added that "demands on defence have
OL,7,Fincreased still further", pointing to
OL,8,Fthe Iran war, threats from Russia in
OL,9,Fthe High North, and escalation in the
OL,10,FUkraine conflict.
OL,12,FThe DIP was expected to be published
OL,13,Fjust ahead of the Nato summit on July
OL,14,F7.
OL,16,FA government source said: "This
OL,17,Fcountry is safer because of the
OL,18,Fdecisions Keir Starmer has made and we
OL,19,Fwill continue to act in our national
OL,20,Finterest.
OL,26,@nD@OOUoD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,F"It is this Labour government and this
OL,7,FLabour Prime Minister that is
OL,8,Fdelivering the largest sustained boost
OL,9,Fto defence spending since the Cold
OL,10,FWar."
OL,12,FThey went on to say that the DIP will
OL,13,F"deliver the capability our armed
OL,14,Fforces need" and that the government
OL,15,F"will always do what is right, and
OL,16,Fneeded, to keep the country safe".
OL,18,FHealey was reportedly only offered #10
OL,19,Fbillion extra for the Ministry of
OL,20,FDefence but he told the PM it would
OL,21,Fnot be enough to keep the country safe.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,FOn Wednesday, Healey was meeting with
OL,7,FAustralian counterparts to step up
OL,8,F"cooperation" on defence including
OL,9,F"sharing vital intelligence" and
OL,10,Fdeveloping new technologies.
OL,12,FLabour MP and Chair of the Defence
OL,13,FSelect Committee, Tan Dhesi said
OL,14,FHealey's resignation "is a grave
OL,15,Fmoment" and said the government "must
OL,16,Ftake that warning with the utmost
OL,17,Fseriousness" and called for a "fully
OL,18,Ffunded" plan.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,FHe added that Healey "has been a
OL,7,Fserious, committed and respected
OL,8,FDefence Secretary" and thanked him for
OL,9,Fhis work.
OL,11,FLeader of the Opposition, Kemi
OL,12,FBadenoch responded saying she was "not
OL,13,Fsurprised" and said the resignation
OL,14,Fwas "honourable".
OL,16,FBadenoch went on to say that "Keir
OL,17,FStarmer's premiership is falling
OL,18,Fapart" and added, "I don't see how he
OL,19,Fcan stay in this job."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781197569
OL,3,CJohn Healey resigns as defence
OL,4,Csecretary over military spending plans
OL,6,FDuring Prime Minister's Questions on
OL,7,FWednesday, Starmer was pressed on
OL,8,Fdefence spending by Badenoch, who
OL,9,Faccused the PM of spending on welfare
OL,10,Finstead of national security.
OL,12,FOn Thursday morning, before the
OL,13,Fresignation, a Downing Street
OL,14,Fspokesperson said that the DIP will
OL,15,Fdeliver the best technology into
OL,16,Ffrontline forces.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
